cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement.Item
      • cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlement.User
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IEntitlementVisitable

    public class User
extends Item
implements IEntitlementVisitable
    Registered Users may call restricted interface methods on each of the cscie97.asn4.housemate.entitlment.IEntitlementServiceAPI, IHouseMateModelServiceAPI, and cscie97.asn4.housemate.controller.IHouseMateControllerServiceAPI services, as long as the User has the appropriate Entitlements. Users may have multiple sets of Credentials, which mean they are able to log in with different sets of usernames and passwords. However, each user may only have a single AccessToken, the ID of which is passed around to the restricted interface methods to ensure the user is authorized to carry out the method being called.
    See Also:
    Credentials, AccessToken
